9},"section":{"name":"UK","uri":"/news/uk"},"site":{"name":"BBC News","uri":"/news"},"timestampRelative":"20 September 2020","publishedDateTime":"2020-09-20T06:33:33.000Z","translations":{"seeAlsos":"More on this story","tagList":"Related Topics","relatedInternetLinks":"Related Internet Links","aroundTheBBC":"Around the BBC","externalLinksWarningText":"The BBC is not responsible for the content of external sites.","socialEmbed":{"instagram":{"warningText":null,"linkText":null},"facebook":{"warningText":"The BBC is not responsible for the content of external sites.","linkText":"View original post on Facebook"},"twitter":{"warningText":"The BBC is not responsible for the content of external sites.","linkText":"View original tweet on Twitter"},"youtube":{"warningText":"Warning: Third party content may contain adverts","linkText":null}}}},"headline":"Coronavirus: £10,000 fines for failing to self-isolate and lockdown life in photos","content":{"model":{"blocks":[{"type":"text","model":{"blocks":[{"type":"paragraph","model":{"text":"Here are five things you need to know about the coronavirus pandemic this Sunday morning. We\'ll have another update for you on Monday. ","blocks":[{"type":"fragment","model":{"text":"Here are five things you need to know about the coronavirus pandemic this Sunday morning. We\'ll have another update for you on Monday. ","attributes":["bold"]}}]}}]}},{"type":"crosshead","text":"1. £10,000 fines for failing to self-isolate"},{"type":"text","model":{"blocks":[{"type":"paragraph","model":{"text":"The government has said it will introduce a new legal duty requiring people in England to self-isolate if they test positive for coronavirus, or are traced as a close contact. From 28 September, those who refuse an order to self-isolate could be fined up to £10,000. The new measures also include a one-off support payment of £500 for those on lower incomes. The PM is still considering tightening restrictions further after a surge in cases across the UK - another 4,422 cases were recorded on Saturday.","blocks":[{"type":"fragment","model":{"text":"The government has said it will introduce a new legal duty requiring people in England to self-isolate if they test positive for coronavirus, or are traced as a close contact. From 28 September, ","attributes":[]}},{"type":"urlLink","model":{"text":"those who refuse an order to self-isolate could be fined up to £10,000.","locator":"https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-54221953","blocks":[{"type":"fragment","model":{"text":"those who refuse an order to self-isolate could be fined up to £10,000.","attributes":[]}}]}},{"type":"fragment","model":{"text":" The new measures also include a one-off support payment of £500 for those on lower incomes. ","attributes":[]}},{"type":"urlLink","model":{"text":"The PM is still considering tightening restrictions further","locator":"https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-54214752","blocks":[{"type":"fragment","model":{"text":"The PM is still considering tightening restrictions further","attributes":[]}}]}},{"type":"fragment","model":{"text":" after a surge in cases across the UK - another 4,422 cases were recorded on Saturday.","attributes":[]}}]}}]}},{"type":"image","model":{"media":{"__typename":"ComponentsImage","originalSrc":"https://c.files.bbci.co.uk/17D5D/production/_114492679_optimised-uk_daily_cases_with_ra_19sep-nc.png","iChefRecipe":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/$recipe/cpsprodpb/17D5D/production/_114492679_optimised-uk_daily_cases_with_ra_19sep-nc.png","height":1875,"width":2666,"alt":"Chart shows daily cases are continuing to rise","loading":"lazy"},"blocks":[{"type":"altText","model":{"blocks":[{"type":"text","model":{"blocks":[{"type":"fragment","model":{"text":"Chart shows daily cases are continuing to rise","attributes":[]}}]}}]}},{"type":"rawImage","model":{"height":1875,"width":2666,"locator":"","originCode":"","copyrightHolder":"BBC","originalSrc":"https://c.files.bbci.co.uk/17D5D/production/_114492679_optimised-uk_daily_cases_with_ra_